stylometry: Safety stock is inventory-on-hand used to prevent a stock out. It is determined based upon the desired service level of a business. A higher service level requires more safety stock. It is important because when weighing the trade off between holding costs and ordering costs, if holding costs are a better option, that is where safety stock comes into play. When demand is very variable, safety stock is also increased. If demand suddenly fluxuates upward, the company will be able to handle the business it recieves, as opposed to losing business because the comapny cannot provide for its customers at all, or at least in an efficient manner.
